column5: how much of that price in california are taxes?
According to the website I've been checking about 26 cents is for California tax and 18 cents is federal.
How much is a litre of gas in Dryden or Sioux Lookout these days?
Dryden prices last week were 99.9 cents per litre. From what I saw most other towns were about the same.
Nice, that is a cool $200 canadian to fill the boat x5 fill ups.....can't wait to get there now. All to bring home 6 fish.
If it's about bringing home fish, your local groceteria will likley have Erie fillets for $9.99/lb Huge savings there.
1 liter = $1 Canadian 1 Canadian dollar = $0.822 US 1 US Gal = 3.79 l. Therefore 1 US gallon costs $3.12 US. Oh well. In the long run we will all be dead so enjoy life when you can.
the lodge probably charges more. to fill half a 5 gallon tank was 17 bucks canadian. fill up at the border.

With all due respect, Norseman.... This is a little like standing outside a roller coaster and saying, "...wait in line for 30 minutes just to go in one big circle..." It's what goes between between point "A" and point "B" that makes it all worth while. If the only vaule you place on your trip is figured via price-per-pound, then I really feel sorry for you.
